---
import CaseStudyMedia from './CaseStudyMedia.astro';
import CaseStudyVideo from './CaseStudyVideo.astro';
import {
  scarlettCaseStudyImages,
  scarlettDemoVideoId,
  scarlettStateMachineVideos,
  scarlettStateOverviewImages,
} from '../../data/scarlettCaseStudy';
import { aboutContactIcons } from '../../data/aboutAssets';
import { contactEmail, socialLinks } from '../../data/aboutContent';

const images = scarlettCaseStudyImages;
const embedUrl = `https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/${scarlettDemoVideoId}?rel=0&modestbranding=1&playsinline=1`;
const backToChapterHref = '/?highlight=scarlet#chapter-1';
---

<article class="scarlett-case-study">
  <header class="scarlett-case-study__hero">
    <p class="scarlett-case-study__project-name">Scarlet</p>
    <h1 class="scarlett-case-study__hero-title">
      An emotional third-person cat adventure about memory, absence, and saying goodbye through <strong>playful interactions.</strong>
    </h1>
  </header>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="scarlett-inspiration">
    <p id="scarlett-inspiration" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">INSPIRATION</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__inspiration-row">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__copy scarlett-case-study__copy--inspiration">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
          What Shaped This <strong>Experience</strong>
        </h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          Since Scarlett left us forever because of cancer, we still feel her presence—imagining
          her as a little ghost playing tricks. This game was born from those cherished thoughts.
        </p>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          In three months, I recreated our home in Unity to visualize Scarlett's presence as a
          playful ghost. By leveraging complex state machines and narrative design to mimic her
          behavior, I turned a personal story into a project that significantly advanced my game
          development fundamentals.
        </p>
      </div>
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__inspiration-media"
        src={images.inspirationShapedPrimary}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Inspiration image 1"
        aspectRatio="516 / 362"
      />
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__inspiration-media"
        src={images.inspirationShapedSecondary}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Inspiration image 2"
        aspectRatio="393 / 257"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="scarlett-game-design">
    <p id="scarlett-game-design" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">GAME DESIGN</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__stack">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
        <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
          Exploration as <span class="scarlett-case-study__title-light">Memory</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
          I designed the home as both a navigable space and a container for memory. Everyday objects, routes, and cat-like interactions gradually reveal the bond between Scarlet and her owners.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__game-design-split">
        <div class="scarlett-case-study__game-design-copy">
          <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
            <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Progressive Interaction</h2>
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
              New abilities are introduced across six days, encouraging players to revisit familiar spaces and reinterpret earlier details. On the final day, they discover that Scarlet is a spirit returning to say goodbye.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
            <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Farewell Through Space</h2>
            <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
              The final sequence reveals that the collapsing home is not a physical disaster, but the owner’s fading dream. As the world unravels, the environment turns emotional loss into a playable farewell before the dream disappears.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <CaseStudyVideo
          class="scarlett-case-study__farewell-media"
          src={images.gameDesignFarewell}
          placeholder="The Farewell gameplay video"
          aspectRatio="16 / 9"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="scarlett-game-development">
    <p id="scarlett-game-development" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">
      GAME DEVELOPMENT
    </p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">
        Actions &amp; Interactions with Player State Machine
      </h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        I built a player state machine for cat-like movement and contextual actions, including jumping, scratching, burying, and object interaction. These behaviours turn ordinary domestic spaces into playable narrative moments.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__state-overview">
      {
        scarlettStateOverviewImages.map((overview) => (
          <CaseStudyMedia
            class="scarlett-case-study__state-overview-media"
            src={overview.image}
            alt=""
            placeholder={overview.placeholder}
            aspectRatio={overview.aspectRatio}
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__state-videos">
      {
        scarlettStateMachineVideos.map((video) => (
          <CaseStudyVideo
            src={video.src}
            placeholder={video.placeholder}
            aspectRatio={video.aspectRatio}
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__subsection">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__subsection-label">ART</p>

      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Visual & Interface Design</h2>

      <div class="scarlett-case-study__art-layout">
        <CaseStudyMedia
          class="scarlett-case-study__art-photo"
          src={images.devScenePhoto}
          alt=""
          placeholder="Real home photo"
          aspectRatio="980 / 624"
        />

        <div class="scarlett-case-study__art-center">
          <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
            I recreated our home as the game’s emotional setting and kept the interface minimal, allowing prompts to guide interaction without disrupting its intimate atmosphere.
          </p>

          <div class="scarlett-case-study__art-ui-row">
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__art-ui"
              src={images.devUiMain}
              alt=""
              placeholder="UI main screen"
              aspectRatio="822 / 624"
            />
            <CaseStudyMedia
              class="scarlett-case-study__art-ui"
              src={images.devUiDetail1}
              alt=""
              placeholder="UI detail 1"
              aspectRatio="912 / 546"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <CaseStudyMedia
          class="scarlett-case-study__art-scene"
          src={images.devSceneGame}
          alt=""
          placeholder="In-game scene"
          aspectRatio="436 / 312"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scarlett-case-study__section" aria-labelledby="scarlett-reflection">
    <p id="scarlett-reflection" class="scarlett-case-study__section-label">REFLECTION</p>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Learning From Playertest</h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        Playtesting showed that the emotional premise was clear, but movement and camera control still needed refinement. Jumping, climbing, and navigating tight interiors required smoother feedback and more consistent handling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__text-block">
      <h2 class="scarlett-case-study__block-title">Remember, Grow, and Move Forward.</h2>
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__body">
        Scarlet was part of my life for three years, and this project became both a technical challenge and a personal farewell. Recreating our home and learning unfamiliar systems gave me a way to preserve her memory, accept her absence, and move forward.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__reflection-media">
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__video">
        <iframe
          src={embedUrl}
          title="Scarlet gameplay demo"
          loading="lazy"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </div>
      <CaseStudyMedia
        class="scarlett-case-study__reflection-photo"
        src={images.reflectionPhoto}
        alt=""
        placeholder="Reflection image"
        aspectRatio="976 / 724"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="scarlett-case-study__footer">
    <a class="scarlett-case-study__back" href={backToChapterHref}>← Back to Chapter</a>

    <div class="scarlett-case-study__closing">
      <p class="scarlett-case-study__thanks">
        Thank you for exploring my world! If it resonates, I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit">
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__name">Hang Wan</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-dot" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__role">Design Playful Experience</span>
        <span class="scarlett-case-study__credit-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <div class="scarlett-case-study__credit-links">
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            aria-label="Email Hang Wan"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.gmail}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            class="scarlett-case-study__credit-link"
            href={socialLinks.linkedin}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="LinkedIn"
          >
            <img
              class="scarlett-case-study__credit-icon"
              src={aboutContactIcons.linkedin}
              alt=""
              width="44"
              height="44"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</article>

<script>
  function initCaseStudyMedia() {
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-img]').forEach((img) => {
      if (!(img instanceof HTMLImageElement) || img.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      img.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = img.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        figure?.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      img.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
      if (img.complete && img.naturalWidth === 0) markMissing();
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('[data-case-study-video]').forEach((video) => {
      if (!(video instanceof HTMLVideoElement) || video.dataset.mediaBound === 'true') return;
      video.dataset.mediaBound = 'true';

      const markMissing = () => {
        const figure = video.closest('[data-case-study-media]');
        figure?.classList.add('is-missing');
      };

      video.addEventListener('error', markMissing);
    });
  }

  initCaseStudyMedia();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initCaseStudyMedia);
</script>
